festival.introText:
Terminal V Festival is back for 2 days this easter featuring a huge lineup of the worlds biggest electronic music acts at our most unique hybrid indoor and outdoor festival site.

Expect incredible mind-blowing indoor stages and further outdoor stages and festival areas alongside techno and house music elitists.

More details and terms & conditions on https://terminalv.co.uk/events/tv2023/

faqs.question: When is Terminal V 2023?
faqs.answer: Terminal V returns to The Royal Highland Centre on Saturday 8th - Sunday 9th April 2023

faqs.question: How much are Terminal V tickets?
faqs.answer: Head to the tickets section to find out the latest ticket prices.

faqs.question: How do I get to Terminal V?
faqs.answer:
By Air - With regular flights connecting Edinburgh Airport to the UK and Europe there are plenty options available. The festival site is a short 10 minute walk from the airport. 

By Car - Public transport is recommended as parking is not available on site. 

By Taxi - There are several local taxi firms to choose from and a taxi drop off point easily accessible by following the signs for the North Car Park.

By Bus - Organised travel is available from Happy Bus and Big Green Coach from several locations direct to The Royal Highland Centre. 24 hour bus services are available with travel across Edinburgh and Glasgow.

By Rail - The closest railway station is The Edinburgh Gateway Station with a 40 minute walk to the festival site. The next closest railway station is Haymarket. 

Terminal V is held at The Royal Highland centre, located on the west side of city, near the grounds of Edinburgh Airport.

Terminal V is easily accessible by coach, shuttle buses and taxis.

Return buses from Edinburgh to Glasgow will be running 24 hours.

The Edinburgh Gateway Station is a 40mins walk from the site for access to trains all over Scotland. Haymarket is the next nearest train station with excellent train links across the UK. For more information contact National Rail on 08457 48 49 50.

The Royal Highland Centre is situated adjacent to Edinburgh Airport. Over 180 flights connect Edinburgh to the rest of the UK and Europe each day and the Royal Highland Centre is just a ten-minute walk from the airport.

There is no parking available for cars, apart from TAXIS, so please do not consider driving to this event

Please follow the signs for the North Car Park. This is also the drop off and taxi pickup point.

Please plan ahead and organise travel plans in advance for leaving arrangements before you arrive at Terminal V.

faqs.question: Where is Terminal V?
faqs.answer: Terminal V is located at The Royal Highland Centre which is close to Edinburgh Airport. The festival site can be accessed easily by taxi, rail and shuttle bus.

faqs.question: Are pre-payment plan tickets available?
faqs.answer: Payment plan tickets are currently not on sale.

faqs.question: Does Terminal V have onsite camping?
faqs.answer: No, Terminal V is a non camping festival so camping equipment is not needed. It is however close to a large choice of accommodation within 1 mile from the festival site.

faqs.question: What happens If I bought a ticket and cannot attend?
faqs.answer:
Unfortunately we can’t issue you with a refund if you can’t make the event due to work commitments or your mates have dropped out. In these circumstances, we advise passing on your tickets privately to avoid losing out on the money spent.

Refunds can only be offered if the event is cancelled or postponed, as agreed upon purchase.

faqs.question: Does Terminal V have any age restrictions?
faqs.answer:
Strictly over 18s (2 forms of ID required). The event is subject to licence and Terminal V's terms + conditions

https://terminalv.co.uk/terms/

faqs.question: Can I bring my own food and drink into Terminal V?
faqs.answer: You are not allowed to bring your own food and drink into Terminal V. There will be a wide variety of food and drink stalls inside the festival, serving up organic, vegetarian and vegan options.
